re Developer)|Tom Lane]]{{spaced ndash}}primary author of [[libjpeg]], major developer of [[PostgreSQL]]\n*[[Sam Lantinga]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of [[Simple DirectMedia Layer|SDL]]\n*[[Richard H. Lathwell|Dick Lathwell]]{{spaced ndash}}co-developer of [[APL (programming language)|APL\\360]]\n*[[Chris Lattner]]{{spaced ndash}}primary author of [[LLVM]] project\n*[[Samuel J Leffler]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Berkeley Software Distribution|BSD]], [[HylaFAX|FlexFAX]], [[libtiff]], [[Comparison of open source wireless drivers#FreeBSD|FreeBSD Wireless Device Drivers]]\n*[[Rasmus Lerdorf]]{{spaced ndash}}original creator of [[PHP]]\n*[[Michael Lesk]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Lex programming tool|Lex]]\n*[[Gordon Letwin]]{{spaced ndash}}architect of [[OS/2]], author of [[High Performance File System|HPFS]] file system\n*[[H\u00e5kon Wium Lie]]{{spaced ndash}}co-author of [[Cascading Style Sheets]]\n*[[Robert Love]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Linux kernel]] developer\n*[[Ada Lovelace]]{{spaced ndash}}first programmer (of [[Charles Babbage]]s' [[Analytical Engine]])\n*[[Al Lowe]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of ''[[Leisure Suit Larry]]'' series\n*[[Hans Peter Luhn]]{{spaced ndash}}hash-coding, linked list, searching and sorting binary tree\n<!-- Please keep entries in alphabetical order. -->\n\n==M==\n<!-- Only add names if the individuals have their own articles, establishing notability. Anything else will be removed.\n     Please keep entries in alphabetical order by last name.  -->\n*[[Khaled Mardam-Bey]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of mIRC (Internet Relay Chat Client)\n*[[Robert C. Martin]]{{spaced ndash}}author of ''Clean Code'', ''The Clean Coder'', signatory on the [[Agile Manifesto]], and leader of the Clean Code movement\n*[[John Mashey]] \u2013 author of the [[PWB shell]], also known as the Mashey shell\n*[[Yukihiro Matsumoto]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Ruby (programming language)|Ruby]]\n*[[John McCarthy (computer scientist)|John McCarthy]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Lisp (programming language)|Lisp]]\n*[[Craig McClanahan]]{{spaced ndash}}original author of [[Jakarta Struts]], architect of [[Tomcat Catalina]] servlet container\n*[[Daniel D. McCracken]]{{spaced ndash}}professor at [[City College of New York|City College]] and author of ''Guide to [[ALGOL|Algol]] Programming'', ''Guide to [[COBOL|Cobol]] Programming'', ''Guide to [[Fortran]] Programming'' (1957)\n*[[Douglas McIlroy]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Macro (computer science)|macros]], [[pipes and filters]], concept of [[software componentry]], [[Unix]] tools (spell, diff, sort, join, graph, speak, tr, etc.)\n*[[Marshall Kirk McKusick]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Berkeley Software Distribution|BSD]], work on [[Unix File System|FFS]], implementor of [[soft updates]]\n*[[Sid Meier]]{{spaced ndash}}author, ''[[Civilization (series)|Civilization]]'' and ''[[Railroad Tycoon]]'', co-founded [[Microprose]]\n*[[Bertrand Meyer]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Eiffel (programming language)|Eiffel]], ''[[Object oriented design|Object-oriented Software Construction]]'', [[design by contract]]\n*[[Bob Miner]]{{spaced ndash}}co-creator of [[Oracle database]], co-founder of [[Oracle Corporation]]\n*[[Jeff Minter]]{{spaced ndash}}psychedelic, and often [[llama]]-related [[video game]]s\n*[[Petr Mitrichev]]{{spaced ndash}}[[competitive programming|competitive programmer]]\n*[[Cleve Moler]]{{spaced ndash}} co-author of [[LINPACK]], [[EISPACK]] and [[MATLAB]] \n*[[Lou Montulli]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of [[Lynx (browser)|Lynx]] browser, [[HTTP cookie|cookies]], the blink tag, server push and client pull, HTTP proxying, HTTP over SSL, browser integration with animated GIFs, founding member of HTML working group at [[W3C]]\n*[[Bram Moolenaar]]{{spaced ndash}}author of text-editor [[Vim (text editor)|Vim]]\n*[[David A. Moon]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Maclisp]], [[ZetaLisp]]\n*[[Charles H. Moore]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of [[Forth (programming language)|Forth]] language\n*[[Roger Moore (computer scientist)|Roger Moore]]{{spaced ndash}}co-developer of [[APL (programming language)|APL\\3