ames\n*[[Leonard Adleman]]{{spaced ndash}}co-creator of [[RSA (cryptosystem)|RSA]] algorithm (the ''A'' in the name stands for Adleman), coined the term ''computer virus''\n*[[Alfred Aho]]{{spaced ndash}}co-creator of [[AWK]] (the ''A'' in the name stands for Aho), and main author of famous [[Compilers: Principles, Techniques, and Tools|Dragon book]]\n*[[Andrei Alexandrescu]]{{spaced ndash}}author, expert C++, D languages\n*[[Paul Allen]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Altair BASIC]], [[Applesoft BASIC]], co-founded [[Microsoft]]\n*[[Eric Allman]]{{spaced ndash}}[[sendmail]], [[syslog]]\n*[[Marc Andreessen]]{{spaced ndash}}co-creator of [[Mosaic (web browser)|Mosaic]], co-founder of [[Netscape]]\n* [[Jeremy Ashkenas]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of the [[CoffeeScript]] programming language and [[Backbone.js]]\n*[[Bill Atkinson]]{{spaced ndash}}[[QuickDraw]], [[HyperCard]]\n<!-- Please keep entries in alphabetical order. -->\n\n==B==\n<!-- Only add names if the individuals have their own articles, establishing notability. Anything else will be removed.\n     Please keep entries in alphabetical order by last name.  -->\n*[[John Backus]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Fortran]], [[Backus\u2013Naur form|BNF]]\n*[[Lars Bak (computer programmer)|Lars Bak]]{{spaced ndash}}virtual machine specialist\n*[[Richard Bartle]]{{spaced ndash}}[[MUD]], with [[Roy Trubshaw]], creator of MUDs\n*[[Kent Beck]]{{spaced ndash}}created [[Extreme programming]] and co-creator of [[JUnit]]\n*[[Donald Becker]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Linux]] [[Ethernet]] drivers, [[Beowulf cluster|Beowulf]] clustering\n*[[Brian Behlendorf]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Apache HTTP Server|Apache]]\n*[[Doug Bell]]{{spaced ndash}}''[[Dungeon Master (video game)|Dungeon Master]]'' series of [[video game]]s\n*[[Fabrice Bellard]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of [[FFmpeg]] open codec library, [[QEMU]] virtualization tools\n*[[Tim Berners-Lee]]{{spaced ndash}}inventor of [[World Wide Web]]\n*[[Daniel J. Bernstein]]{{spaced ndash}}[[djbdns]], [[qmail]]\n*[[Eric Bina]]{{spaced