hort]]{{spaced ndash}}prolific writer of [[Interactive fiction]] and co-developer of [[Inform]] version 7\n*[[Jacek Sieka]]{{spaced ndash}}developer of [[DC++]] an [[open source software|open-source]], [[peer-to-peer]] [[file sharing|file-sharing]] [[client (computing)|client]]\n*[[Ken Silverman]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of [[Duke Nukem 3D]]''{{'}}s graphics engine\n*[[Charles Simonyi]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Hungarian notation]], [[Bravo (software)|Bravo]] (the first [[WYSIWYG]] text editor), [[Microsoft Office Word|Microsoft Word]]\n*[[Colin Simpson (author)|Colin Simpson]]{{spaced ndash}}developer of [[CircuitLogix]] [[simulation software]]\n*[[Rich Skrenta]]{{spaced ndash}}co-founder of [[DMOZ]]\n*[[Matthew Smith (games programmer)|Matthew Smith]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Sinclair ZX Spectrum]] games, including ''[[Manic Miner]]'' and ''[[Jet Set Willy]]''\n*[[Henry Spencer]]{{spaced ndash}}[[C News]], [[Regex]]\n*[[Joel Spolsky]]{{spaced ndash}}co-founder of Fog Creek Software and [[Stack Overflow]]\n*[[Quentin Stafford-Fraser]]{{spaced ndash}}author of original [[Virtual Network Computing|VNC]] viewer, first Windows VNC server, client program for the [[Trojan room coffee pot|first webcam]]\n*[[Richard Stallman]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Emacs]], [[GNU Compiler Collection|GCC]], [[GDB]], founder and pioneer of [[GNU]] Project, terminal-independent I/O pioneer on [[Incompatible Timesharing System|ITS]], [[Lisp machine]] manual\n*[[Guy L. Steele Jr.]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Common Lisp]], [[Scheme (programming language)|Scheme]], [[Java (programming language)|Java]]\n*[[Alexander Stepanov]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of [[Standard Template Library]]\n*[[Christopher Strachey]] \u2013 draughts playing program\n*[[Ludvig Strigeus]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of [[uTorrent]], [[OpenTTD]], [[ScummVM]] and the technology behind [[Spotify]]\n*[[Bjarne Stroustrup]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of [[C++]]\n*[[Zeev Suraski]]{{spaced ndash}}co-creator of [[PHP]] language\n*[[Gerald Jay Sussman]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Scheme (programming language)|Scheme]]\n*[[Herb Sutter]]{{spaced ndash}}chair of the ISO [[C++]] standards committee and C++ expert\n*[[Gottfrid Svartholm]]{{spaced ndash}}co-creator of [[The Pirate Bay]]\n*[[Aaron Swartz]]{{spaced ndash}}software developer, writer, Internet activist\n*[[Tim Sweeney (game developer)|Tim Sweeney]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Unreal (1998 video game)|The Unreal engine]], [[UnrealScript]], [[ZZT]]\n<!-- Please keep entries in alphabetical order. -->\n\n==T==\n<!-- Only add names if the individuals have their own articles, establishing notability. Anything else will be removed.\n     Please keep entries in alphabetical order by last name.  -->\n*[[Amir Taaki]] \u2013 Leading developer for the [[Bitcoin]] project\n*[[Andrew S. Tanenbaum|Andrew Tanenbaum]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Minix]]\n*[[Audrey Tang|Audrey \"Autrijus\" Tang]]{{spaced ndash}}designer of [[Pugs (programming)|Pugs]]\n*[[Simon Tatham]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Netwide Assembler|NASM]], [[PuTTY]]\n*[[Larry Tesler]]{{spaced ndash}}the [[Smalltalk]] code browser, [[debugger]] and object inspector, and (with Tim Mott) the [[Gypsy (software)|Gypsy]] word processor\n*[[Jon Stephenson von Tetzchner]]{{spaced ndash}}co-creator of [[Opera (web browser)|Opera]] web browser\n*[[Avie Tevanian]]{{spaced ndash}}author of [[Mach (kernel)|Mach kernel]]\n*[[Ken Thompson]]{{spaced ndash}}main designer and author of [[Unix]], [[Plan 9 from Bell Labs|Plan 9]] and [[Inferno (operating system)|Inferno]] operating systems, [[B (programming language)|B]] and Bon languages (precursors of [[C (programming language)|C]]), creator of [[UTF-8]] character encoding, introduced [[regular expression]]s in [[QED (text editor)|QED]] and co-author of the [[Go (programming language)|Go programming language]]\n*[[Michael Tiemann]]{{spaced ndash}}[[G++]], [[GNU Compiler Collection|GCC]]\n*[[Linus Torvalds]]{{spaced ndash}}original author and current maintainer of [[Linux]] kernel and creator of [[Git (software)|Git]], a source code manage