bert Watson (computer scientist)|Robert Watson]]{{spaced ndash}}[[FreeBSD]] network stack parallelism, [[TrustedBSD]] project and [[OpenBSM]]\n*[[Pei-Yuan Wei]]{{spaced ndash}}author of [[ViolaWWW|Viola]], one of the earliest graphical browsers\n*[[Peter J. Weinberger]]{{spaced ndash}}co-creator of [[AWK]] (the ''W'' in the name stands for Weinberger)\n*[[Jim Weirich]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of Rake, Builder, and Ruby Gems for [[Ruby (programming language)|Ruby]]; popular teacher and conference speaker\n*[[Joseph Weizenbaum]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of [[ELIZA]]\n*[[David Wheeler (computer scientist)|David Wheeler]]{{spaced ndash}}co-creator of [[subroutine]]; designer of [[WAKE (cipher)|WAKE]]; co-designer of [[Tiny Encryption Algorithm]], [[XTEA]], [[Burrows\u2013Wheeler transform]]\n*[[Arthur Whitney (computer scientist)|Arthur Whitney]]{{spaced ndash}}[[A+ (programming language)|A+]], [[K (programming language)|K]]\n*[[why the lucky stiff]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of libraries and writing for [[Ruby (programming language)|Ruby]], as well as a quirky and popular [[Why's (poignant) Guide to Ruby|guide to learning programming]]\n*[[Bruce Wilcox]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of Computer Go, programmed NEMESIS Go Master\n*[[Evan Williams (Internet entrepreneur)|Evan Williams]] \u2013 creator and co-founder of [[Logo (programming language)|Logo programming language]]\n*[[Roberta Williams|Roberta]] and [[Ken Williams (game developer)|Ken Williams]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Sierra Entertainment]], ''[[King's Quest]]'', graphic adventure game\n*[[Sophie Wilson]]{{spaced ndash}}designer of instruction set for [[ARM architecture|Acorn RISC Machine]], author of [[BBC BASIC]]\n*[[Dave Winer]]{{spaced ndash}}developed [[XML-RPC]], Frontier scripting language\n*[[Niklaus Wirth]]{{spaced ndash}}[[Pascal (programming language)|Pascal]], [[Modula-2]], [[Oberon (programming language)|Oberon]]\n*[[Stephen Wolfram]]{{spaced ndash}}creator of [[Mathematica]]\n*[[Don Woods (programmer)|Don Woods]]{{